variables.value: Come on in to Café Tank and grab a "tankful" of treats! Hehehe.
The day I lost it... I went to the Shopping District Arcade,\nthe Port factories, and the park near school!
You have to find it! That's an order!
I kinda wanna\njoin a club, but...
There's so many\nto pick from, huh.
But I also wanna watch\nbaseball games...
Now that I'm at <MNT:NAGUMOHARA>, I wanna join a club and make memories.\nBut I'd hate not having time to cheer on the baseball team.
I really wanted that limited-edition CHAMP-ON top...\nBut I hesitated over the size, and then they sold out.
How'd you get your hands on one?\nGosh, I'm so jealous.
Watching <LST:YAGYU> out there... he was way more dazzling than I imagined.\nMaybe it's okay if I start cheering for the football team instead?
You could join the wind orchestra club—they play at games.\nBut the captain's a huge <LST:YAGYU> fan and super strict.
Geez, that's why I told ya to grab it while you could!\nNow we just gotta pray for a restock.
CHAMP-ON's sneakers are all the rage too.\nIf you rock the whole set, you'll be a style icon!
Honestly? I was thinking the same thing!\nThey've got a bunch of popular guys too! Let's be their top fans!
Oh, you go to <MNT:NAGUMOHARA>, don't you?\nI hope you're enjoying your classes!\nMy kids might follow in your footsteps someday.
Did you go to a cram school?\nI wonder if I should start sending my kids...\n<MNT:NAGUMOHARA> doesn't sound easy to get into...
They say even Tristar elites and CEOs' daughters go to <MNT:NAGUMOHARA>.\nMaybe I should work on my manners now—just in case.
Excuse me—don't just barge in like that.\nI don't want someone like you setting a bad example\nfor the children.
Balancing sports and academics sounds tough,\nbut <MNT:NAGUMOHARA> really manages it. I'm impressed.
Academically, West Manor is a good choice.\nBut when it comes to clubs, it's no match for <MNT:NAGUMOHARA>.
My husband and I both went to Northbright,\nso I'm curious what private schools are like these days.
I want my kids to grow up in a diverse environment.\nMaybe Eastwind International could be the right fit...
AI Academy's in Chubu, but they're using AI to teach smarter,\nnot harder. Sounds like the future, and might be worth considering.
I heard Royal Academy lets students run the football club themselves.\nThat boy genius <LST:ALICE>? He looked like a straight-A student too.
Making it to the finals on their first try?\n<MNT:NAGUMOHARA> is really something. Even as a Northbright alum,\nI'm cheering them on!
<MNT:NAGUMOHARA> is a very promising school.\nI want to try on the uniform!
But I like my tutor... Hmm, I guess I'm okay\nwith going to cram school just for the summer!
I dunno about <MNT:NAGUMOHARA> anymore...\nbeing around all those brainiacs sounds kinda suffocating.
Wait, you're from <MNT:NAGUMOHARA>? You look like trouble,\nbut you're smart too? That's kinda cool, actually!
<FUL:MIKA> and <FUL:YUKI> are joining the football team in junior high.\n<MNT:NAGUMOHARA> doesn't have one, right? Hmm, what should I do...
They say if you can't decide on a school,\njust pick the one with the best uniform.\nI'm totally into the blazers at <MNT:NAGUMOHARA>!
I was all about the <MNT:NAGUMOHARA> blazers,\nbut those Northbright sailor uniforms are actually super cute!
I didn't know schools could just shut down.\nThe Northbright kids must be so sad.
This super quiet guy dropped a flashy afro wig earlier.\nBet he's secretly an InaTuber or something.
Royal Academy's one of the top schools,\nbut it gives off serious military vibes. Kinda scary, honestly.
Raimon's full of kids trying to go pro, right?\nMust be nice having that kind of talent.
Pass the exam, get into <MNT:NAGUMOHARA>, and the rest is smooth sailin'.
I got an A on my mock exam the other day.\nThis'll be a piece of cake.
I heard <MNT:NAGUMOHARA> treats their teachers well.\nNo wonder the education's top-notch.
Oh, I know you. You're that delinquent from <MNT:NAGUMOHARA>, right?\nPretty sure that outfit's against the dress code.
If I get into <MNT:NAGUMOHARA>, joining the baseball club's a must.\nBalancing school and a top-tier club? That's the golden path.
I'm pretty sure I could get into <MNT:NAGUMOHARA> or West Manor.\nBut hey, whichever's closer feels like the safer pick.
With the birthrate dropping, a lot of schools can't even fill seats.\nMakes entrance exams sound kinda easy, don't it?
If <MNT:NAGUMOHARA> ditches the middle-high school combo, that's a downgrade.\nBut overall, it's still the better pick for clubs.
AI Academy's the one in Aichi, right? If your parents are down,\nyou get to study AI and everything. Not a bad deal.
So the Noble Insight Institute players really do have that aura, huh?\nI heard they've got grads that teachers are always name-dropping.
<MNT:NAGUMOHARA> made the finals? For real? If they win,\nand I get in—yeah, I'm totally joining the football club!
I always buy PWR Protein Bar from this machine,\nbut it's been sold out lately. Did someone buy 'em all?
The tropical energy drink's only sold at the school store, right?\nThink they'll ever put it in a vending machine?
<FST:RAIKA> posted about some really tasty snack online...\nI want to try it too, but I can't remember what it's called.
Huh... didn't think someone like you used vending machines, <FLC:SAKURAZAKI>.\nWere you getting something? You can go first!
I'd treat you to a drink, you being a freshman and all...\nBut since you were the center of that mess... maybe next time.
My favorite sports drink's been sold out forever.\nGuess it blew up after that announcer <FLC:TABE> talked about it on TV.
They were selling them\njust the other day...
My favorite energy drink's been sold out forever.\nGuess it blew up after that announcer <FLC:TABE> talked about it on TV.
I just can't focus without that stuff.\nHope I can find it somewhere...
Whoa! The energy drink I've been craving!\nIs it really for me?! Thanks a ton!
Ah, thanks for waiting!\nAll restocked now, so help yourself!
That's quite a striking hairdo you have there...\nIs that the fashion among youngsters nowadays?
That sports brand called CHAMP-ON...\nThey say the young folks nowadays just call it "CHAMP."
I saw a young lad wearing what they call a "hoodie" the other day.\nThe dress code at <MNT:NAGUMOHARA> is fairly relaxed, then?
You've got quite the bold style, young man...\nWas that wild hairstyle something you were born with?
These days, I've noticed more young people going to that Café Tank.\nCould this be what folks call a "retro boom"?
I hear this game called Mekkemon is quite popular now.\nThink an old-timer like me should give it a try?\nPerhaps I'll ask my grandson.
Everyone seems to be abuzz with Football Frontier these days...\nI heard Eastwind International is making quite a splash\non their very first try!
The noodle shop in the shopping district's popular with students.\nMaybe I'll drop by and say hello to <FST:CHINAMI>—it's been a while.
I saw some young folks taking pictures of that Chilling Ice Cream.\nSeems like that's quite the thing these days.
In an article about the grand finals,\nthere was a photo of a child holding a stuffed rabbit.\nIs that sort of thing popular with young people these days?
I hear quite a few popular shops have popped up\nat Odaiba Football Gardens. I wonder if that\nfootball-patterned burger I saw years ago is still there.
I'm too nervous to enter the shop...\nBut I want to try out their castella parfait sooo badly!
This has to be\na bad idea...
The castella parfait here is divine, so I'm back for more!\nAt this rate, the staff will remember me!
I heard the staff gets to eat castella parfait for free,\nso I applied for a job here. I hope I get in...
What am I gonna\ndo with you...?
Mom's gotta get home\nand make dinner...
It's all thanks to\nthat nice lady!
That song just sticks\nin your head...
It's really stuck\nin my head now...
That game's all the\nrage these days.
But you don't even\nknow the characters!
Just one more and I'll complete the whole set!\nI want every single Spooky Bigbums!
Hurry and crank it or someone else will snatch it!\nI even saw a grown woman playing it yesterday!
One more and I'll have the full Spooky Bigbums set!\nYou think that lady who pulled a bunch would trade with me?
I finally got the full Spooky Bigbums set!\nThat glasses lady traded with me!
This Spooky Bigbums sings when you press its belly!\nI wanna finish the whole set fast!
The new Spooky Bigbums set is awesome!\nThey all sing different songs! I want 'em all!
They made a new Sameowrai keychain, but I don't have it yet!\nI wanna take it to daycare!
This weird gorilla sticker isn't cute at all! I don't like it!\nWho stuck that on the capsule machine?
Clingkong's so cute!\nI want the strap!
I started playing Mekkemon on Mommy's phone!\nI know every character in this capsule machine!
Just one more and I'll have the whole Mekkemon set!\nBut I kinda wanna try the other machines too...
My daughter's obsessed with this character called Spooky Bigbums.\nIt's starting to worry me... Though I used to collect stuff myself.
I don't really get what's so special about Spooky Bigbums,\nbut I hear grown-ups like it too.
I get wanting to complete the set, but it's tough.\nMaybe if she finds someone to trade with, she'll calm down a bit.
Someone traded her the last one she needed.\nGuess even grown women like Spooky Bigbums.
I heard every character in this set sings a different tune.\nStuff like this just makes you wanna collect 'em all...
Thanks to my daughter, that Spooky Bigbums song's stuck in my head...\nNow I kinda want the whole set too.
I'm all for supporting the shopping district,\nbut I wish mascot merch was a little easier on the wallet...
A gorilla with a rice bowl...? What a weird sticker.\nSomeone must've stuck it on as a prank.
I get it's cute, but if you start buying stuff from games\nyou don't know, it never ends.
I said no to toys from games she doesn't know, and now she won't\nquit begging me to play Mekkemon. That backfired big time.
My daughter started playing Mekkemon,\nbut now I'm the one who's hooked...\nI won't rest until I pull DragonDrake!
Let's pick some up\non the way home.
That snack I had out\nin the countryside...
First, we gotta\ntaste it and learn!
Let's make it better\nthan the store's.
Bacon and eggs\nare a must too.
They say getting the\nfoam right is key.
Let's simmer it until it\nmelts in your mouth.
Should we try\nmaking it at home?
We'll need a big pot\nfor sure.
Gotta make sure\nthe broth is perfect.
[向/む]かって[右側/みぎがわ]の[道/みち]が　[繁華街/はんかがい]です。
I swear, I just can't put Mekkemon down...
Some thugs seem to be planning revenge on someone.\nAt least, that's what the cats seem to be saying.
I've heard there's a young man with a dark expression who shows\nup at Seaside Park sometimes. Or so the cats say... I think.
They say there's a boy at <MNT:NAGUMOHARA> Junior High who often\ncares for the cats. The cats enjoy watching his magic tricks.
A large group seems to have entered the cats' territory.\nPerhaps they're students from Northbright Academy?
To celebrate <MNT:NAGUMOHARA>'s victory, the diner handed out canned food.\nThe cats are benefiting from your efforts, too.
A fisherman at the harbor gave out horse mackerel after\n<MNT:NAGUMOHARA> won. Your winning streak lifts everyone's spirits.
To celebrate reaching the finals,\nthe fishmonger gave the cats some tuna.\nThat's more lavish than what we get at home!
I wanted to join the esports club, but my parents said no way.\nThey think a club that's just about playing games isn't worth it.
Esports isn't just messing around.\nThere's world championships and all.\nI wish Mom could see how awesome it really is...
Wait, I'm not talking about you, <FLC:SAKURAZAKI>!\nThis has nothing to do with you!
I wanted to join the occult society, but my parents shut that down too.\nThey say if I mess with spooky stuff, bad luck will come my way.
I heard the occult stuff actually teaches a lot about history\nand culture, which sounds cool. But Mom just won't listen at all...
Then there's the metal club I wanted to join, but again,\nparents said no. They think it's some punk rock thing.
The metal club's actually about studying ores and minerals—not music.\nBut they totally misunderstood, and I doubt I can explain it now.
Alpine nails it again!\nThey're really good.
I'm fed up with the\nshopping district...
This plan to build a shopping center keeps getting dragged out...\nDoesn't seem like folks 'round here want anything new.
How long do we\nhave to wait?
It's been ages since I heard about that <MNT:NAGUMOHARA> resort project...\nWhat in the world are those Tristar Holdings folks doing?
Honestly, what's the\npoint of all this...
We just don't see\neye to eye, I guess.
Looks like some are against the shopping center...\nMostly the shopkeepers in the district, from what I hear.
Why on earth would\nanyone be against it?
You can watch matches\non your phone...
Just wish I could\nsee it live...
